Class Vertex

All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable
public class Vertex
extends GeometryComponent
implements java.lang.Comparable

Represents a vertex in the edge of a polygon shell in a coverage. A vertex can be adjusted to a new coordinate value. The vertex implements some heuristics to limit the adjustment. It maintains an ajustment tolerance, and will not adjust the vertex further than this tolerance. This is set to half the length of the smallest segment incident on the vertex, the idea being to eliminate the possibility of the endpoints of a segment being adjusted to "cross over" one another.
